An original story. By OSCAR FAULHARER, Professor of German, Phillips Exeter Academy, N. H. (34 pages. Cloth. Price, by mail, 18 cents. Intro- duction price, 15 cents.

HIS story is a picture of German life in its variety, describing the

features of different classes of political, civil and military soci- ety. The military life bears on the historical period of Napoleon I. The book touches upon the education of youth in that period, upon national festivals, social life, travel, customs, traditions, and art as found in the galleries, with glimpses ot German history, and refer- ences to other historical events. Words of foreign origin, unless thoroughly incorporated in the language, have been carefully avoided; the purity of the Saxon or Germanic idiom is maintained; the con- structionis not too complicated, and the style, changing from descrip- tive to narrative, will afford the student excellent drill in translation or in reading at sight, and will secure a rich and varied vocabulary, a matter of prime importance to the students wishing to thoroughly

appreciate the spirit of German literature.
